rest_of_day_open: I have alot to accomplish and goals to fulfill. critical_positive: I believe what worked well about the conversation was using visual context clues to what my conversation partner would be interested in discussing and allowed us to have a genuine and engaging conversation. This was better than aimlessly having a conversation and helped shift it without too many awkward spaces and silences.
critical_negative: Hmmm I believe if I was to truly find something that didn't work the "best" was that I felt like I leaded the conversation mainly but I consider myself a conversationalist so that didn't bother me too much because I chose to take the lead. Maybe also the demographic being randomized and I didn't see us sharing any demographic characteristics led me to lead the conversation to make sure none of my personal privacy or comfort was infringed on as a woman of color.

rest_of_day_open: Well, I have a dentist appointment tomorrow to get a permanent crown put on, which will make me look a little better so that's a big plus. I also have to run some errands and the heat index here is on par with death valley temperatures for the next several days, so that'll be rough. To sum it up, i'd say mixed.
critical_positive: Letting my conversation partner take the lead more, made it smoother than when I was just chatting along. Talking about common interests like body mods and video games really made the time go by fast also. Talking about current events also seemed to be a pretty easy topic to respond to.
critical_negative: For the most part it all worked out really well. I will say I was cut off a couple of times and my conversation partner had quite a bit to say where occasionally I couldn't get a word in edge wise, but that didn't happen often enough to make the conversation bad.
